{
  "text": "Note that taking the limit n → 1, S n approaches the conventional von Neumann entanglement entropy. For integer n, there is an explicit prescription to compute these entropies using path-integral techniques [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . One introduces the replica manifold M n , which is an n-sheeted covering of the original (Euclidean) spacetime manifold branched along the region A (see Fig. 5 ).",
